highlights.description: KC: Moving to Madison from Chicago-- it seemed safer, but was the first place I dealt with racism
When Donald Trump won the presidential election, my 9-year-old asked me if it meant we were going to be slaves again
We need to prioritize diversity in our schools
Moms talking about their kids of color responding to Donald Trump winning 2016 presidential election

Monica tells a childhood story where she was harassed by kids, a fight emerged, and the police came to her door, angry. Describes the tired feeling of having the same cop pull her over again and again.
